{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648283","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648283"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:52:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:52:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18306"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18306"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11024"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78523"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11024","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11024"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18306"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63864"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7236"},{"type":"tags","id":"7238"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25585"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25589"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26899"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78523","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78523"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the apex of the popliteal fossa the sciatic nerve bifurcates into the tibial and common fibular nerves.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is innervated by the common fibular division?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gastrocnemius","Long head of biceps femoris","Semimembranosus","Semitendinosus","Short head of biceps femoris"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe sciatic nerve is a major nerve of the lower limb, composed of two divisions: the tibial and the common fibular. It provides motor and sensory innervation to various parts of the leg.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eshort head of the biceps femoris\u003C/strong\u003E is innervated by the common fibular division of the sciatic nerve. This is distinct from the long head of the biceps femoris, which is innervated by the tibial division of the sciatic nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESemitendinosus\u003C/strong\u003E - Innervated by the tibial division of the sciatic nerve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESemimembranosus\u003C/strong\u003E - Innervated by the tibial division of the sciatic nerve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELong head of biceps femoris\u003C/strong\u003E - Innervated by the tibial division of the sciatic nerve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastrocnemius\u003C/strong\u003E - Innervated by the tibial nerve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe common fibular nerve primarily innervates muscles in the anterior and lateral compartments of the leg, but it also innervates the short head of the biceps femoris in the posterior compartment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The common fibular division of the sciatic nerve innervates the short head of the biceps femoris muscle.","The sciatic nerve is composed of two divisions: the tibial and the common fibular.","The common fibular nerve primarily innervates muscles in the anterior and lateral compartments of the leg."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Giuffre BA, Black AC, Jeanmonod R. Anatomy, Sciatic Nerve. 2023 Nov 16. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29494038."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63864"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18306"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63864"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-11T09:19:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-11T09:19:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11024"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78523"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I